						               													<description>Frankenstein:  Madmen and Monsters is an asymmetric hidden Roles Board Game, based on the Frankenstein Mythos.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Take the role of character from the book/movies created by Mary Shelley and reach your unique objective before anyone else and change the tragedy we all know (or make it worse!).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player take a secret character and a hand of 3 resource cards. The first player to achieve the goal of it&amp;acute;s character wins and the game ends!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is divided in 3 phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Collect, In which you play a card to gather resources with an unique system that allows you to receive resources from adjacent players (you give them resources too).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Hire, You will hire a service in one of the 8 available locations (2 possible actions per location), which will be resolved in the next phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Interlude: You can reveal your secret character to activate an unique power and get close to your objective.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Survive, The hired actions resolve in location order, hurting some players, protecting others or giving you that advantage you need to achieve victory&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Includes 8 characters with gorgeous illustrations, each with a different goal and power, 8 locations to hire different effects, 32 ticket cards to manage resources (with an unique balance mechanic) and 8 player boards to track resources.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
